=== Translog production function ===
The translog production function is an approximation of the CES function by a second-order Taylor polynomial in the variable formula_63 about formula_64, i.e. the Cobb–Douglas case. The name translog stands for &quot;transcendental logarithmic.&quot; It is often used in econometrics for the fact that it is linear in the parameters, which means ordinary least squares could be used if inputs could be assumed exogenous.

