<doc id="350690" wikidata="Q240018" url="?curid=350690" title="Kazik Staszewski">
<text>Kazimierz Piotr Staszewski (born 12 March 1963), also known as Kazik, is a Polish singer and songwriter. He is the son of the architect and poet Stanisław Staszewski. He is the frontman of the band Kult, which he founded in 1982; their latest album, &quot;Ostatnia Płyta&quot;, was released in 2021. In 1991, he launched a solo career with one of the first Polish rap albums, &quot;Spalam się&quot;.

Staszewski was also member of other bands (El Dupa, Bulldog, Zuch Kazik, Kazik na Żywo&quot;).&quot; He continues to work with Kwartet ProForma.

